🏺 The Khalkeia (Χαλκεῖα), a festival of crafts-people, was celebrated today in honor of Athena and Hephaistos\n\n
Today (2023-Nov-14) is Maimaktēriṓn 1, νουμηνίᾳ Μαιμακτηριῶνος, day 120 of 354 in the year 2023/2024.
This Maimaktēriṓn will have 29 days, which the ancient Greeks called a “hollow month” (κοῖλος μήν) as opposed to a “full month” (πλήρης μήν) of 30.
